caption: This morning, I went to this coffee shop to get my morning coffee before going to work. This coffee shop served the best latte in town, better than any other. They even have cookies, muffins, and donuts, all of which were delicious! This place is a coffee lover's dream come true. It is highly recommended that you visit this place.

Stopped in to get an Off The Menu Club special and was super pleased. The tikka roll was really delicious. Also got a mango lassi and two samosas. Flavors were super fresh and everything was delicious. I ordered vegetarian and they were really helpful making sure I got tofu instead of chicken. 10/10 would buy again

I went to this coffee shop this morning, to have my morning coffee before coming to work. This coffee shop was having the best Latte than any other coffee shop in the city. They also offer cakes, muffins, and donuts, which were very tasty …
Best coffee shop in Burbank! The red head working today brightened the day of anyone that walked in. Keep up the good work
I love love love this coffee house! Andy and Dave were so great during my last visit . They're  always so friendly and make the best coffee. A must go to place for a cup of joe! Highly recommended!

I found out about Home cafe from their IG page, noticing how appealing their latte arts are! Latte art is just a bonus, their menu is unique and have a lot of items that most cafes/coffee shops don't have!
Have been coming here for years, still one of the best restaurants in LA. Food, staff, atmosphere - - all fantastic! And especially the Montecristo sandwich, the best ANYWHERE!
Best diner in Montrose, quick friendly service. The skillets and biscuits are bomb. Vegetarian options are on the smaller side and could leave you wanting more but everything else is great.

I've been here twice (both times while my cousin was in town visiting,) but I feel like we tried everything! This place is AMAZING! I feel like it's a hidden gem, along with the rest of Montrose and the quaint little neighborhood it's …
Had a bit of time to kill this morning and so I decided to stop by for breakfast! The place was pretty crowded around 9:30am but there were still some seats outside.

Hands down the best Indian you can find in LA. From the soup to the naan (get the parm naan!) to the Balti and the Korma. I dream of this restaurant. No idea how it's so empty when I go (between 2 and 6 usually). Prices are very reasonable. …

One of my favorite places to stop by in Alhambra and order one of my favorite drinks the Passion Fruit Royal Tea!!  I always order the basil popcorn chicken and lobster balls!! Never fails to fill me up!  Super friendly staff, quick service …

DRNK coffee + tea is a lovely casual cafe that has a clean breakfast, offering only a few toasts, bowls and sandwiches to choose from. That said, their items are done very well - my bf and I both enjoyed the lox toast and their special bowl …

I'm so happy that I found this hidden gem about a year ago now! I used to take classes at Club Pilates and I stumbled upon them on my way back home. The owner is so nice and they have the nicest and sweetest employees!! Plus, their coffee …

Only down side is that they don't do any substitutions...even on the easy stuff for health reasons...And they're inconsistent- some cashiers will allow it but the mangers is hardcore, unfriendly and when he's around he never allows it. …

I haven't even been but already this is a five star place for sure, Lexi was pleasant when I called, I ask if they were playing a certain game, she reassured they were. When I explained we were bringing my 85 year old father in law for his …
Melanie was exceptional!!!  Ordered the breakfast burrito at in was so good!!!  Love this place!!!

My favorite boba shop in the city. Every drink I have tried is high quality, just like their boba. Consistently liked shop and conveniently close to USF. Bo baristas are always friendly, kind, and determined on trying to give you your order …

My friends recommended Philz for coffee, they come here several times a week. It was my first time, and they recommended I try the mint mojito iced coffee. It was different, very cooling and refreshing. I don't think I would go out of my way to come here but if I was in the area I would drop by again to try other drinks.
This place is clean, consistent, and makes an awesome Green Giant!
I love this place not only for its location but also for the excellent service that they offer
The best coffee in Sunset. Friendly crew at work with great owner and manager. Would definitely visit again soon
Mediocre coffee and TERRIBLE parking and seating area..go elseware!
Never been to a tea place but looks legit.  They brew it at the right temp for the right time, taste amazing!
the selection of food is very awesome and good!

This place took forever to open and now I see why. I walked in at 3:30 on a Wednesday to grab a sandwich from the case and go. There was 1 employee making multiple juices for waiting customers! That's B A N A N A S! Isn't that the whole …
DRNK coffee + tea  is my go-to coffee shop. If you are every in the area, this place is a must. I love their avocado toast and almond croissant.

Nice neighborhood bar by the lake.. popular with locals. can get quite crowded most evenings but nice drinks, though last visit they couldn't make the one drink I go there for called the Green Lush... said they didn't have  the ingredients ready... booo!  DRNK coffee + tea

I had some time to kill before my salsa class next door. It wasn't much time so a place DRNK coffee + tea , was a must. I stumbled upon this place on a Monday night hoping for a warm drink to fight off the cold weather chills. Unfortunately …

Very good burger! Reminded me of a DRNK coffee + tea. But juicier and tastier. I had the True Cheesy Burger and my wife had the True Deluxe burger! Both were amazing and we ordered Crispy Garlic fries with them. All in all this was a really …
I need cream!  this is the strongest cup of coffee ever !  i love the jolt of caffeine without the bitter acidic taste like some other handmade coffee joints  i've had.
Can't go wrong with either coffee or tea!
Love this spot. Everyone who works here are great :) I usually take my coffee to go. When I have some spare time I will sit and enjoy a cappuccino in their little outdoor benches.

Came here on a Saturday morning to get some studying done. The place doesn't look like much from the outside but inside is amazing! Plenty of seating, good Wi-Fi, and plenty of outlets. BONUS: GREAT COFFEE.  Everything I want is a study spot. Will definitely be coming back
Good lattes and nice environment! I've had the matcha latte with soy milk, the iced chai latte and a regular latte and all have been well done!
This DRNK coffee + tea is really good, it has a really nice creamy texture to it. Wish we had more branches from these coffee shops... the coffee gets my 4 star.....not cheap but worth it...

Hidden jem for fast, fresh food - not just drinks as the name implies. Awesome turkey sandwich. A few tables inside and outside to grab a quick or get food to go. Very reasonably priced - my sandwich was huge, delicious and under $8.
First timer here and I'm satisfied with my  S'Blendid coffee. Worth it before work.
One of the best macchiatos I've ever taste... Excellent service btw. Oh! And if you're hungry you can try the blue bottle sandwich, it's so delicious.
First time.  Latte is glorious, delicious, smooth, creamy, yummy, delightful, perfect, wonderful, and noteworthy.
We have a blue bottle coffee in CA , when I moved to the bay I definitely still needed my fix. I stop in about once a week, and I'm never let down!

Stopped here for a quick drip coffee and I was impressed by the quick, friendly service! I got a drip more on the medium roast side, and it was just the pick-me-up I needed after feeling slightly jet-lagged. I ended up sitting here for a …
My favorites place to go to get my acai bowl fix!
I live next to here but has never been inside. Very cozy and welcoming. Staff were nice and helpful, but a little ditsy.
A very nice place, nice coffee and smoothies
Cute place with great tea, coffee selections. Their tea party combo is a good deal! Highly recommend to anyone who enjoys local café vibes and tea culture.

Really good coffee shop ! the wait can be pretty long at times, but it's a must try (at least once). i got the drink on the bottom, it's the Cookie Monster but iced and it's one of my favorites. The one on the top is Birthday Cake which is really good too. Good coffee shop overall !

Delicious coffee  to be enjoyed on alley! I was walking on the alley to avoid the morning crowd, little coffee board sign made me curious to check it out! It wasn't busy, ordered a latte, the guy made it quick and beautiful. Take a sit and enjoy the flavor of this aromatic drink!

I m a coffeeholic, i need coffee to feed my life almost every single day. I have to say this is the best soy latte I ve ever tried in the financial district!! The taste of the coffee blended well together with the soymilk, and it tasted so silky and smooth.
prices that are reasonable.
We love DRNK coffee + tea and have been wanting to try the breakfast. Had the benedict and waffle....Delish!

My wife and I walk here and enjoy their New Orleans Iced Coffee on our day off together.  The coffee is always good, the staff is nice and the place has a nice atmosphere.  Their whole bean coffee is a little pricey, but it is worth it to …
Love their Nitro coffee. Decided to go another route with the vanilla latte today and is was great! They also have a number of delicious smoothies to choose from.

Very trendy , just the way you want a coffee shop to be! Their New Orleans style iced coffee was perfect , not too sweet , herbal tea was amazing too.  I thought the service was friendly ..but more on the serious side.

They’re located like in tiny ‘plaza’ where you can also get stuff like smoothie bowls. I got iced latte and mozzarella salad, which was very fresh with good amount of cheese and veggies. Coffee was delish, stuff nice and chill. Would …

I was looking for a local coffee place while I was walking in Market St, and this place showed it. It is hidden, but thanks to the phone GPS I did not get lost. I ordered their filtered/distilled coffee. It unique, and has a bold sweet taste. I wish this place can open another place to where I live!

First time here & all I had heard about this spot was the rainbow latte... which I wasn't keen on trying. I got the lavender jasmine tea latte... and it is GOOD. Pleasantly surprised! Creative lattes are fun options to mix it up!

Ok ok lemme preface this by saying I don't drink coffee normally. But pictures of their lattes look amazing so I had to try it. The inside of this cafe is extremely cozy and cute, and the lattes are straight up beautiful. Definitely the best cafe I've ever stepped foot in!
How cute is this little shop?!? So friendly!! Great place to drop by and grab a quick drink or bite!  I recommend the Senorita well worth it! Wish we had one of these in Vegas.
Went here twice while in LA, better than average coffee and friendly service.

Awesome siphon coffee shop! Coffee was $6 for 12oz. The barista was so helpful and knowledgeable, and they had a great selection. Atmosphere was peaceful. The smell of freshly ground coffee fills the air. A great place to relax.
Good food and drinks. But I don’t know, could this stuff gays make my sandwich even more slowly than they did... Do not recommend if you’re in a hurry.
Great service, great drinks, pretty ladies working the counter lol
I loved absolutely everything that DRNK had to offer. I'm sure that, if anyone went in there, they'd find something that they like.
Good strong coffee. Late hours. Convenient location.
Love the N Acai Bowl!!
Awesome place great environment love the food and the chai blanc
Delicious drinks and food wonderful customer service great atmosphere to relax and lose track of time. Can't wait to go back and try something new.

Wow, this is probably the best coffee in Los Angeles.  Seriously amazing.  Coffee snobs and serious foodies will be blown away by the Kyoto brew.  They also offer flights for those too weakminded to make a decision.  The interior is modern …

Great little coffee shop, the barista was incredible. They have 6 different on tap coffee & tea. I had a nitro cold brew coffee, and my wife had a low acid hot coffee. Very awesome place highly recommended it.

My sweet husband brings me treats from this particular spot. I haven't been disappointed yet. I just had a nibble of a triple chocolate cookie & a jalapeno & cheese bagel with cream cheese. omg. yes, that good.
Iced green tea is delicious
I love it
Hip place. Very nice atmosphere friendly baristas. Good coffee, sandwiches and organic juice.
Its an awesome place
No just no
Whatever I say I don't say enough. Amazing staff, friendly, huge huge selection of products. And their bagels are one of a kind. I order 2 jalapeno bagel and a latte and they just hit the spot.
The smoothies are very tastier than expected!
Great Coffee shop for breakfast. Nice Coffee and croissants. Kind staff
Great coffee shop, drink I've tried was so delicious and super fresh. I'll definitely back to try for more.
Love. This. Place!
I liked the Natural Juice they have and prepared sandwiches...
QWENCH IS THE SPOT!! Tourists wanna find a great refreshing drink forget the "others" come here better quality AND!! Fair prices
Delicious coffee & great atmosphere.
Friendly service good high energy.  They brew coffee for 18hrs for ice brew.  They also have a nitro brew and several teas on tap! Many sandwiches and drinks to choose from.
Chai Blanche... nice profile, but too sweet for my personal taste. But this is a nice coffee place and worth stopping by
GREAT coffee... Good smoothies, but disappointingly they are NOT organic fruits and veggies which is not great since you are likely drinking them for health when they are made with pesticides.
They have the best tea in here
I LOVE THEIR ICED COFFEE!!! It is my favorite place in Hollywood, WAY above Starbucks or Coffee Bean. And its affordable unlike most of the other coffee shops.
Coffee is great in there, better than in Starbucks and Coffee Bean for sure. Kind of like in Peet's, I would say, which I like as well.
